The paper deals with calibration of multiple sensors in a robotics and mapping system, which is a common problem in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The sensors mentioned in the paper include cameras (cs.CV) and lidars (cs.RO), which are commonly used in robotics and mapping applications. The proposed method involves graph optimization (cs.LG), which is a common technique used in robotics and computer vision. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques (cs.AI) to improve the calibration results.
